Currently with cap being a boolean, `mapValuesWithKey` can be converted via the following

``` js
// capIteratee only works when the iteratee is first.  This isn't the case for
//   some functions.  It also ignores rearg'd iteratees
const capIteratee = fp.curry((cap, fn) =>
  fp.curryN(fn.length, (iteratee, ...args) =>
    fn.apply(null, [fp.ary(cap, iteratee)].concat(args))
  )
);
const mapValuesWithKey = capIteratee(2, fp.mapValues.convert({ cap: false })));
```

This could be more concise by making cap an integer:

``` js
const mapValuesWithKey = fp.mapValues.convert({ cap: 2 });
```

